	   <tr><td colspan=2>Thanks to the kindness of Max from Mythrilmoon Mystics, who killed the werewolf I was tracking right in front of me, I was able to loot this.  It was him, an iksar monk, and myself at the scene when the wolf with this drop went down.  Since I was the priest class, I was able to loot it, yay! <br><br>I was really happy because I saw a reed belt for sale earlier today, but someone wanted 3k.  I didn't have or want to spend 3k for a belt upgrade from the crystalline belt.  So, this just worked out super. This belt has the same stats pretty much and a little bonus, too,<br><br>A lot of the people during this event were really nice, and they didn't loot and destory the items.  Many tried to be careful about KS'ing too.  I was only KS'ed twice, and that's not bad.  Instead ruining the loot that wasn't for their class they let someone around them try to loot it, or if no one was around, they gave locs over shout and ooc.  It's nice to know that so many people in a zone can work together.  They even held out on killing the boss mob right away, and the WC GM event lasted most of a day and until 4am game time. :)<br><br>The only other druid or general priest class item I heard of that dropped during that event was the Pegasus Feathered Headdress.  That's cute too! But I have an Othmir Fur Cap, so as cute as that item sounds, I'm glad I got the belt. :)<br>&nbsp;<br>Cylestria Shimmeringspring<br>Druidess of Tunare - 31st Season<br>&lt;Radiant Circle&gt; Seventh Hammer</td></tr>
